Our eyelids are screens that protect the eyeball from the many small particles that settle on them.
Forgetting about the regular cleaning of the eyelids, we often contribute to the development of blepharitis.
The output is simple:
Do not rub your eyes with dirty hands, wear a special wet wipe for the eyelids;
At least 1-2 times a day, clean the edges of the eyelids from the accumulated harmful substances during the day.
Cleaning procedures are not superfluous to complement and warm compresses with decoctions of medicinal herbs (salt, chamomile), diluting the dense secretion of sebaceous glands, and then massage the edges of the eyelids, which should be carried out in circular movements of the finger pads;
rinsing makeup, do not use alcohol-containing means.
They dry and dehydrate the skin and contribute to an even greater thickening of sebaceous gland secretion.
