Moving to a hostel can range from slightly acting on the nerves to absolutely frightening.
He encourages you to talk: tell people where you came from, whether you took your academic leave and where you spent it, whether you support Corbyn and why you "honestly, do not love, do not hate Marmait, because, seriously, guys, it's just a yeast extract HAHAHA, I'll be at home."
Take a break.
And help others rest too - ask questions and show interest.
This keeps you talking and helps you find the people you like, not the ones you wouldn’t even talk to, even if your eyelashes were lit and they were giving out fire extinguishers.
Give people space.
People’s rooms often turn into drinking establishments, midnight cinemas, and common hangouts, but they’re also a place where people dress up and fix their underwear.
Don’t even think about starting a university while in a relationship.
Introverts in universities are treated unfairly.
