Try to feel when a classmate is tired of communicating - and not to knock on him, but to send an SMS.
By the way, about knocking: do it.
A guy in my dorm followed this principle: if the door was not locked, then he was invited to enter.
He saw something.
Make friends with baking.
As you begin university life at the peak of Bake-Off’s popularity, knocking on people’s doors to introduce yourself and present a plate of chocolate biscuits is no longer such a strange action, not so reminiscent of the 1950s with their “Welcome, we’re neighbors, I’ve baked you something, and now smile, and I’ll ask you personal questions.”
