This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers "Top 1000 Russian Managers" comes out for the 16th time.
As a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian senior managers, the study summarizes the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of last year’s rating winners.
The winners of last year are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate of the rating of the current year and to nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates included in the initial list is proposed to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, which it would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following managers of the functional areas of the company: CFO, Commercial Director, Marketing Director, HR Director, IT Director, Director of Public and Corporate Relations, Director of Relations with Authorities, Director of Corporate Governance.
Each proposed by experts manager is invited to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate their management team and up to ten new managers from other companies.
The nomination of candidates on the basis of the industry principle is carried out on the basis of the industry classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, forestry and woodworking industry, mechanical engineering, media business, metallurgy, multidisciplinary holdings, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, transportation, trade
Each participant is provided with a login and password to log into the site www.top1000.amr.ru, where they see information about other participants and can make their assessments according to the proposed criteria for each functional direction.
The methodology of rating construction is based on the principle "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
This principle allows you to obtain the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at meetings of expert commissions.
All wishing candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of past years are invited to full-time meetings of expert commissions.
The commissions are organized on a functional basis: the commission for approval of the list of senior managers and eight commissions for approval of heads of functional directions.
At the meetings of expert commissions, it is proposed to approve the submitted lists in alphabetical order (places are kept strictly according to the online assessment and are closed information before the publication of the rating) or to make updating their adjustments according to the attached list of standby candidates.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Kommersant".
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
The comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the market for lending to small and medium-sized businesses in January-April this year fell by 40%.
What do you think the situation is today?
After the panic at the end of 2014 - the beginning of 2015, SME lending volumes decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Loans below 25-30% per annum were not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could put in an increased rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-refunds, now it is impossible to do it: rates and so cloudy.
For business, the current level of SME loan rates is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their payback.
A rate of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and generate attractive returns on them.
How much do you think the demand for loans is being met?
After the lowering of the CB interest rate, the situation improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, the business does not understand the prospects of its development and future revenues.
Today, business has one solution: it is necessary to learn how to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, to monitor the movement of money.
At the same time, if there are financial resources, it is worth using new technologies that allow to modernize equipment, reduce production costs and energy supply.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends in the SME lending market that will strengthen and affect its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for lowering the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator demonstrates consistency in the issue of lowering the key rate.
However, a radical fall in the price of loans for SMEs should not be expected.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes it necessary to raise the interest rate to generate real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even if the rates of the Central Bank are reduced.
If we talk about the level of overdueness, then traditionally small and medium-sized companies, limited both in the possibilities of replenishment of funds and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the proportion of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country’s economy.
