Often the men who come to us feel unable to talk to their friends.
The old teaching of “live with it” is strong, as is the feeling that frank conversation about problems can be perceived as weakness.
Friends is one of those shows that comes to mind when I try to offer longer-lasting coping mechanisms.
It highlights the inconspicuous moments of male friendship.
As for my task, the status of an outsider on the phone helps people in moments of despair, and long-term support comes from the immediate circle of family and friends.
So if you’re visiting FriendsFest at Comedy Central this weekend, where you’ve completely restored the scenery for the holiday, why not take your friends for a drink at Central Perk.
