One of the most obvious reasons for them was the unprecedented migration crisis, which swept the EU countries some time ago.
So, in Germany already overcrowded all points intended for accommodation of refugees.
On the eve of the country's authorities decided to temporarily settle migrants in the territory of the former concentration camp Buchenwald.
