Where can I leave feedback on the work of the bailiff in Murmansk?
The Office of the Federal Service of bailiffs in the Murmansk region reported that to improve the work on the protection of the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations in the department there is a book of reviews and proposals.
In it, citizens can leave a record of the quality of the work of bailiffs-executors and other officials of the administration, information about shortcomings in the work, as well as express their suggestions and wishes.
A copy of the book of reviews and suggestions is in the central hall, in a special pocket in a visible and accessible place at the checkpoint to the building.
In the structural management units, the book is in the office.
Taking into account the nature of the withdrawal or proposal, where necessary, a written response shall be sent to the initiator.
Xi Jinping calls for a more open economy for the world
The economy needs to become more open to the world to spur its growth, President Xi Jinping said Tuesday in a speech to a group facing the challenge of leading reforms.
"China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop a policy of openness," he said, addressing participants in the 16th meeting of the Committee of the Central Lead Group on Comprehensive Deepening of Reforms.
According to him, expanding openness and deepening reforms will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide a new space for economic development.
The lead group adopted a number of directives, including introducing regulation of investor access to the market, changing the rules of border control, encouraging public enterprises (SOE) to attract private capital and revising the registration system of residents.
According to the statement, a list of sectors of the economy and production that are not available for investment will be compiled.
The system will be gradually debugged through trial programs.
This is an important step as it will give the market a more meaningful role in allocating resources, ensuring business legitimacy and increasing openness, the statement said.
The government will also loosen control over the powers it gives to companies, ensuring that companies run their own businesses.
The statement also said China would allow border regions to develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to boost local growth.
Even more areas will be available to private investors in order to increase the openness of government-controlled sectors of the economy.
“The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of foreign-funded companies, as well as provide them with better conditions,” the statement said.
The procedure for applying for a permanent residence permit for foreigners, or “green card”, will be further facilitated by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the filing process itself.
The meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of lawyers and training of professional judges and prosecutors.
According to the official report issued after the meeting, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli.
